         <div xml:id="main">
            <head type="incipit">
               <supplied reason="XTF-compatibility">15/1/83 ¶  ¶ I am again very obliged to you, noble Friend, for the information that you have given us about several consignments of algae. Mr Bracebridge Wilson is away on a holiday journey. He will b...</supplied>
            </head>
            <p rend="number" xml:lang="de">83.01.15a</p>
            <p rend="correspondent" xml:lang="de">To Jacob Agardh</p>
            <p rend="location" xml:lang="de">Handskr. <seg style="">Avdl., Universitetsbibliotek, Lund, Sweden.</seg>
            </p>
            <space dim="vertical" unit="lines" quantity="1"/>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-family: Geneva; font-size: 12pt; text-align: end; "
               xml:lang="de">15/1/83.</p>
            <space dim="vertical" unit="lines" quantity="1"/>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-family: Geneva; font-size: 12pt; "
               xml:lang="de">
               <seg style="">
                  <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>Ich bin Ihnen wieder sehr verpflichtet, edler Freund, für die Auskunft, welche Sie uns über mehrere Algen-Sendungen gegeben haben. Mr Bracebridge Wilson ist fort auf einer Ferien-Reise. Er wird sich besonders freuen, dass er ein neues Genus entdeckt, und dass Sie seinen Namen specifisch damit verbunden haben.</seg>
            </p>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-family: Geneva; font-size: 12pt; "
               xml:lang="de">
               <seg style="">
                  <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>Es ist auch besonders dankenswerth, dass Sie so viele Exemplare zurück-senden, aber ich bitte Sie besonders, ja </seg>
               <seg style="">
                  <hi rend="underline">irgend</hi>
               </seg>
               <seg style=""> specimina zurück zu behalten, welche Interesse für Sie haben mögen, und für Ihre </seg>
               <seg style="">
                  <hi rend="underline">eigne</hi>
               </seg>
               <seg style=""> Sammlung werthvoll sind.</seg>
            </p>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-family: Geneva; font-size: 12pt; "
               xml:lang="de">
               <seg style="">
                  <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>Es ist viel besser, dass seltne Algen-Exemplare in die Sammlung des </seg>
               <seg style="">
                  <hi rend="underline">grössten Kenners</hi>
               </seg>
               <seg style=""> über gehen, als dass solche zu uns zurück-kommen. </seg>
            </p>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-family: Geneva; font-size: 12pt; "
               xml:lang="de">
               <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>Verehrungsvoll der Ihre</p>
            <p rend="valediction"
               style="font-family: Geneva; font-size: 12pt; margin-left: 1.75in; margin-right: 0in; text-indent: 0in; "
               xml:lang="de">Ferd. von Mueller.</p>
            <space dim="vertical" unit="lines" quantity="1"/>
            <space dim="vertical" unit="lines" quantity="1"/>
            <space dim="vertical" unit="lines" quantity="1"/>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-family: Geneva; font-size: 10pt; text-align: end; "
               xml:lang="en">15/1/83</p>
            <space dim="vertical" unit="lines" quantity="1"/>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-family: Geneva; font-size: 10pt; "
               xml:lang="en">
               <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>I am again very obliged to you, noble Friend, for the information that you have given us about several consignments of algae. Mr Bracebridge Wilson is away on a holiday journey. He will be particularly pleased that he has discovered a new genus and that you have connected his name with it specifically.<note xml:id="ftn1" type="footnote" n="1">
                  <p rend="Footnote"
                     style="font-family: Geneva; margin-left: 0.3335in; margin-right: 0in; text-indent: -0.3335in; font-size: 9pt; "
                     xml:lang="en">See M to J. Agardh, 1 January 1883, where he acknowledged the list of identifications, namely J. Agardh to M, November 1882 (in this edition as 82-11-00a). The new genus and species collected by J. B. Wilson at Port Phillip Heads was published in <seg style="">Agardh (1873-90), part 5, p. 67 as</seg>
                     <seg style="font-style: italic; ">Callipsygma wilsonis</seg>
                     <seg style="">.</seg>
                  </p>
               </note>
            </p>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-family: Geneva; font-size: 10pt; "
               xml:lang="en">
               <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>It is also particularly commendable that you return so many specimens, but I ask you particularly to retain <seg style="">
                  <hi rend="underline">any</hi>
               </seg> specimens that may have interest for you and are valuable for your <seg style="">
                  <hi rend="underline">own</hi>
               </seg> collection.</p>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-family: Geneva; font-size: 10pt; "
               xml:lang="en">
               <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>It is much better that rare specimens of algae pass into the collection of the <seg style="">
                  <hi rend="underline">greatest specialist</hi>
               </seg>, than that they come back to us.</p>
            <p rend="valediction"
               style="font-family: Geneva; margin-left: 1.75in; margin-right: 0in; text-indent: 0in; font-size: 10pt; "
               xml:lang="en">Respectfully your</p>
            <p rend="valediction"
               style="font-family: Geneva; margin-left: 1.75in; margin-right: 0in; text-indent: 0in; font-size: 10pt; "
               xml:lang="en">
               <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>Ferd. von Mueller</p>
         </div>
      </body>
